I"Ý<p>If <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/lax-information-hygiene-norms-beg-memetic-attacks">a meme is passive, yet highly contagious</a>, then it can easily <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/public-opinion-formation-is-memeplex-propagation">propagate</a> throughout <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/information-hygiene-is-like-spacecraft-sanitization">a globalized society</a>. However, if some trigger mechanism is activated, say by <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/beliefs-are-gates-into-the-body-s-biochemistry">retrospective interaction with new beliefs</a>, then that <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/foresight-guidance-memeplex">meme</a> might become actively dangerous.</p>
